II. 1  The origins of the functionalist perspective can be traced to the work of Herbert Spencer and Emile Durkheim. 2  The problem of maintaining social order is a central problem for understanding society. 3  Understanding society from a functionalist perspective is to visualize society as a system of interrelated parts.
